200B;⁠⁠‎&#8206;&#8206;​‌‎‎&#8206;&#8288;‌​​&#8288;n‎&#8203;&#8205;&#8203;​‌&#8205;&#8203;‍﻿﻿&#8206;&#x200B;​&#8205;⁠‍‍⁠&#8204;‎&#8204;&#8205;&#8288;‍&#8204;&#8204;&#8204;&#8206;&#8288;​﻿⁠&#8288;‍‍⁠&#8205;&#8205;⁠s‎‌&#8205;&#8204;‎&#8205;&#8288;⁠﻿&#x200B;⁠&#8206;&#8204;​&#8204;​&#8205;​&#8204;&#8206;⁠‎&#8288;&#8204;&#x200B;‎⁠‍⁠‍&#8206;&#8204;​‎​&#8204;&#8205;&#8205;&#8206;‍​‍⁠&#8204;
        ```bash
        #!/bin/bash
        #set -x
        trap 'echo "Aborted due to Ctrl-C"' INT

        #Get all execution directory IDs in the current folder and loop over them.
        for i in `ls -d [0-9]*`
          do
            echo "####################"
            echo "### Execution id: "$i
            cd $i

              # Look for all the sqlout*_err.txt and sqlout*_out.txt files.
              echo "### Error output"
        	 find . -name 'sqlout*_err.txt' -print -exec cat {} \;
              echo
              echo "### Standard output"
        	 find . -name 'sqlout*_out.txt' -print -exec cat {} \;
              echo

            cd ..
          done;
        ```

        ```bash
        #!/bin/bash

        # Copy all of the files from the cardconnect_conversion/sql folder to the
        # execution folder that will be used by this process.

        #Get the current executionID.
        execID=`ls -d [0-9]*`

        #Go to the card connect conversion sql folder.
        cd cardconnect_conversion/sql

        #Get all the statements.
        for stmt in `ls *.sql`
          do
                #Copy each statement
        	cp $stmt ../../$execID/$stmt
          done;

        cd ../../$execID
        ```

        ```bash
        #!/bin/bash
        #set -x
        #trap 'echo "Aborted due to Ctrl-C"' INT

        ###################
        # Usage: ./importids.sh IDSTOIMPORT.TXT
        #
        # This script will import list of IDs to convert from a text file, formatted as one ID per line.
        #
        #       The list will be renamed to ALLIDS.TXT
        ##################

        # Validate the number of arguments.
        if [ $# -ne 1 ]
          then
        	echo "ERROR: Incorrect number of arguments. This script requres 1 argument, the IDs text file."
        	echo "       Usage: ./importids.sh IDSTOIMPORT.TXT"
          exit 1;
        fi

        #Get the import file name.
        importidsfile=$1

        # Make sure that the file specified exists in the directory.
        if [ ! -f ${importidsfile} ]
          then
          echo "ERROR: "$importidsfile" could not be found, please validate the import IDs file."
          exit 1;
        fi

        #Get the current executionID.
        execID=`ls -d [0-9]*`

        #Copy the import ids as a backup file.
        cp ${importidsfile} ${execID}/

        #Rename the import file to allids.txt.
        mv ${importidsfile} ${execID}/allids.txt

        #Change to the directory.
        cd ${execID}
        ```

        ```python
        #!/usr/bin/python
        import os
        import sys
        import time
        import subprocess


        ####################
        # Main script to run all of the SQL statements found in this directory.
        #       SQL statements are located in the current folder named *.sql and
        #      are executed in name order.
        #
        #      Each sql statement output is saved into two (2) log files:
        #               sqlout[sqlfilename]_out.txt - Contains standard output
        #               sqlout[sqlfilename]_err.txt - Contains error output
        #
        #     The SQL*PLUS output is also redirected to nul for standard output for
        #     cleanliness.  Error output, if any, will be displayed on the screen
        #     for troubleshooting.
        #
        ####################

        #Variable statements.
        curdir = os.getcwd()
        idfile = "allids.txt"
        numprocs = 0
        maxprocs = 25

        #Function to execute sql statements.
        def run_sql(stmt,sqlout_fileout,sqlout_fileerr):
                sqlplus = subprocess.Popen(["sqlplus","-s","user/password@database"], stdin=subprocess.PIPE, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE)
                sqlplus.stdin.write("WHENEVER SQLERROR EXIT SQL.SQLCODE;\n")
                sqlplus.stdin.write("set linesize 2000;\n")
                sqlplus.stdin.write("set pagesize 2000;\n")
                sqlplus.stdin.write("set serveroutput on;\n")
                sqlplus.stdin.write("@"+stmt+";\n")
                sqlplus.stdin.write("exit;\n")
                (sout, serr) = sqlplus.communicate()

                # Check for any standard output to file.
                if sout is not None :
                        outfile = open(sqlout_fileout, 'wb')
                        outfile.write(sout)
                        outfile.close()

                # Check for any error output to file.
                if serr is not None :
                        errfile = open(sqlout_fileerr, 'wb')
                        errfile.write(serr)
                        errfile.close()
                return;

        # Make sure that the allids.txt file exists.
        if not os.path.isfile(idfile):
            print "ERROR: All IDs file ("+idfile+") could not be found, please run importids.sh first."
            sys.exit(1)

        #Get all the statements and loop through them to submit multi-threaded.
        allstmts = [f for f in os.listdir('.') if os.path.isfile(f) and f.endswith('.sql')]
        allstmts.sort()

        #Loop over statements and submit.
        for stmt in allstmts:

            # Get current count of processes running.
            while(numprocs >= maxprocs):
                time.sleep(2)
                numprocs = subprocess.check_output("ps -ef | grep \"sqlplus\" | grep -v grep | wc -l", shell=True)
                numprocs = int(numprocs)
                print str(numprocs)+" current sqlplus processes"

            #Get the current count of processes running.
        #    print "Preparing SQL statement: "+stmt
            numprocs = subprocess.check_output("ps -ef | grep \"sqlplus\" | grep -v grep | wc -l", shell=True)
            numprocs = int(numprocs)
            print str(numprocs)+" current sqlplus processes"

            #Submit the job.
            print "  Submitting SQL statement: "+stmt
            sqlout_fileout = "sqlout"+stmt.split(".")[0]+"_out.txt"
            sqlout_fileerr = "sqlout"+stmt.split(".")[0]+"_err.txt"
            run_sql(stmt, sqlout_fileout, sqlout_fileerr)

        #Wait for processes to complete
        print "Waiting for all processes to complete...."
        while(numprocs > 0):
            time.sleep(5)
            numprocs = subprocess.check_output("ps -ef | grep \"sqlplus\" | grep -v grep | wc -l", shell=True)
            numprocs = int(numprocs)
            print str(numprocs)+" current sqlplus processes"

        #Completed.
        print "All processes completed!"
        ```
